<BODY BACKGROUND='Image1.jpg'><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Sacred Name King James           
Version</H3><P><A HREF='B54C001.htm'>1st Timothy 1</A></P><CENTER><H2           
ALIGN=CENTER>The First Epistle of Paul to Timothy</H2></CENTER><P><A            
HREF='index.htm'>Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5  
WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter 2</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>I exhort therefore, that, first of  
all, supplications, prayers, intercessions, and giving of thanks, be made for   
all men;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>For   
kings, and for all that are in authority; that we may lead a quiet and          
peaceable life in all godliness and honesty.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A 
NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>For this is good and acceptable in the sight of   
ELOHIYM our Saviour;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD> 
<TD><P>Who will have all men to be saved, and to come unto the knowledge of the 
truth.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>For     
there is one ELOHIYM, and one mediator between EL and men, the man MASHIYACH    
YAHSHUA;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>Who   
gave himself a ransom for all, to be testified in due time.</P></TD></TR><TR>   
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>Whereunto I am ordained a       
preacher, and an apostle, (I speak the truth in MASHIYACH, and lie not;) a      
teacher of the Gentiles in faith and verity.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A 
NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>I will therefore that men pray every where,       
lifting up holy hands, without wrath and doubting.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD         
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>In like manner also, that women     
adorn themselves in modest apparel, with shamefacedness and sobriety; not with  
broided hair, or gold, or pearls, or costly array;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD         
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>But (which becometh women         
professing godliness) with good works.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A       
NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>Let the woman learn in silence with all         
subjection.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P> 
But I suffer not a woman to teach, nor to usurp authority over the man, but to  
be in silence.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD> 
<P>For Adam was first formed, then Eve.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A      
NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>And Adam was not deceived, but the woman being  
deceived was in the transgression.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15> 
<H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P>Notwithstanding she shall be saved in childbearing, if   
they continue in faith and charity and holiness with sobriety.</P></TD></TR>    
